                <div class="removal-reason">
                    <strong>Why removed:</strong> 65% < 70% threshold<br>
                    <strong>Evidence:</strong> Grade B-C (observational studies only)<br>
                    <strong>Issue:</strong> Association doesn't prove causation. Reverse causation possible (dementia ‚Üí less sun exposure ‚Üí lower vitamin D). Confounding by healthy lifestyle not ruled out.
                </div>
