                        <strong>Prior:</strong> 0.55 (based on observational association)
                    </div>
                    <div class="bayesian-step">
                        <strong>Evidence Update 1:</strong> Ghahremani (2023) observational<br>
                        40% risk reduction (n=12,388), but self-selection bias likely<br>
                        ‚Üí Posterior: 0.55 ‚Üí 0.65 (BF = 2.5)
                    </div>
                    <div class="bayesian-step">
                        <strong>Evidence Update 2:</strong> Finnish RCT (2025)<br>
                        Non-significant trend, underpowered (only 45 cases)<br>
                        ‚Üí Posterior: 0.65 ‚Üí 0.50 (BF = 0.59, weakens confidence)
                    </div>
